Post-Match Reflections: I think there’s a lot to be proud of with the team from a growth standpoint.
It felt really, really good to battle through a tough moment and pull out a win here at home.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Thursday’s victory over the reigning Western Conference Champions was highlighted by Utah’s ability to pull out a win during crunch time, with key buckets and defensive stops coming in the final minutes to secure the win.

Although it was two veterans in Jordan Clarkson and John Collins who put the finishing touches on the game, Utah closed with Keyonte George and Kyle Filipowski on the floor, two 21-year-olds adjusting to life in the pros.
Following the victory over Dallas, Utah is 2-1 in clutch games this season with a slightly positive net-rating, an impressive start to the season in such situations given the team’s youth.
